Hi Stan,
Tube type bulbs?  Sounds like a floresent bulb installation.  The original 
Westie interior lights used standard one filament automotive bulbs.

> #3) The interior parts were just floating loose, stacked in the van when I 
> got it.
> There was no sink (I can live with that).

Never was one.

> There was no Ice Box or water tank. (I can live with that too).

There should have been one of each.

> There was no Stove (I don't like that).

There were none installed in pre-1968 VW buses.  Get a Coleman two or three 
burner.

> What could I expect to see in a 66 Westy with walk through seats?

A walk thru interior.

